Defendant Theresa Ann Rodriguez in court with attorney Matthew Lamke.  Defendant Theresa Ann Rodriguez in custody.  Katherine M Halopka-Ivery appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  vk  Defendant changes her plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to her plea, advised of her Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, jury instructions and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
Sentencing proceeded. Statements by state, defense and defendant. 
Court orders sentence withheld and placed the defendant on 1 year probation with the following conditions:
- random UAs
- no further citiations for loiter or for prostitution
- provide a DNA sample
- pay all court costs inclusive of the DNA surcharges 
Court costs due and owing by 2/15/2017 or civil judgment.
